<HL>
   Vencor Inc. 2nd-Quarter Net
</HL>
<DATE>
06/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   VCOR
</CO>
<LP>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- Vencor Inc. said it expects
second-quarter net income to be about 10 cents a share.
Year-earlier net was two cents a share.
   Vencor said the increase reflects improved results at two
hospitals recently acquired by the company. The company,
which specializes in providing long-term hospital care for
patients who suffer from catastrophic illness, expects to
release results in late July.
</LP>
