<HL>
   Business Brief -- American Healthcare Management:
   Dallas Company Will Move
   Base to Philadelphia Area
</HL>
<DATE>
06/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   AHI
</CO>
<LP>
   American Healthcare Management Inc. said it will move its
corporate headquarters from Dallas to a western suburb of
Philadelphia by Oct. 1.
   Steven Volla, president of the operator of hospitals, said
the move will allow the company to take on a new management
team in the wake of its emergence late last year from
reorganization under federal bankruptcy laws.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Volla said about 15 members of American Healthcare's
current management team will relocate to the Philadelphia
area, and about 35 people working in the Dallas office will
be laid off.
</TEXT>
