   Business Brief -- Homestead Holding Corp.:
   CCNB to Acquire Company
   For $17.8 Million in Stock
</HL>
<DATE>
06/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CCNC HMSD
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)
</IN>
<LP>
   Homestead Holding Corp. said it signed a letter of intent
to be acquired by CCNB Corp., a New Cumberland, Pa., bank and
thrift holding company, in a stock transaction valued at
about $17.8 million.
   Terms of the proposed transaction call for holders of
Homestead common to receive CCNB stock valued at about $15.48
per Homestead share. Homestead, a savings bank holding
company based in Middletown, Pa., has about 1.2 million
common shares outstanding.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Gary L. Holman, president of Homestead, said the agreement
is subject to a number of conditions, including approval by
regulators and Homestead shareholders.
   Homestead has assets of about $259 million and equity
capital of about $18 million, Mr. Holman said. CCNB has
assets of about $1.2 billion, he said.
